8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 793, L.D. 1188, “An Act to Include
10 Harness Racing with Other Sports for Purposes of Sports Wagering”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Amend the Law Governing Facilities Approved by the State Harness
13 Racing Commission to Sell Pari-mutuel Pools and Common Pari-mutuel Pools for
14 Simulcast Racing'
15 Amend the bill by striking out the emergency preamble and substituting the following:
16 'Emergency preamble. Whereas, acts and resolves of the Legislature do not
17 become effective until 90 days after adjournment unless enacted as emergencies; and
18 Whereas, Maine harness racing is an important historic sport; and
19 Whereas, attracting new fans to Maine harness racing is critical to the future well-
20 being of the industry and agriculture; and
21 Whereas, the 2025 racing season commenced in April and this legislation must take
22 effect as early in the 2025 racing season as possible; and
23 Whereas, in the judgment of the Legislature, these facts create an emergency within
24 the meaning of the Constitution of Maine and require the following legislation as
25 immediately necessary for the preservation of the public peace, health and safety; now,
26 therefore,'
27 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and before the
28 emergency clause and inserting the following:
29 'Sec. 1. 8 MRSA §275-B, sub-§3, as amended by PL 2023, c. 51, §1, is further
30 amended by repealing the 2nd blocked paragraph.
31 Sec. 2. 8 MRSA §275-B, sub-§4 is enacted to read:
32 4. Facilities approved by commission; track located in another county. The
33 commission may authorize a facility approved under subsection 3 to continue operation in
Page 1 - 132LR1038(02)
